      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 58,
      "message": "Without this, I get\n\n  Error: unable to build kubernetes objects from release manifest: error validating \\\"\\\": error validating data: unknown object type \\\"nil\\\" in PersistentVolume.metadata.labels.type\n\nSo I assume the checking is stricter with either the new k8s or helm versions, as this worked before without specifying this value.  Judging by the name (/dockerdata-nfs) the only other value that appears to make sense is \"nfs\".\n\nAdditional information of values can be found at https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/storage/persistent-volumes/#types-of-persistent-volumes.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6874,
        "name": "Todd Malsbary",
